SIMULATION CONFIGURATIONS:
Default simulation configuration: compares the behaviour of the NeuroML model versus NEURON model, in a single comparment cell and in the Solinas's model.
pacemaking_figure2: normal behaviour
rebound_figure3: increased firing rate after hyperpolarization
Ihblock_figure5A: pacemaking activity reduced
subthreshold_figure9A: without the spike generating channels the pacemaking activity is slower
phase_reset: a spike induced by a current injection reset the phase of the pacemaking activity
phase_reset_noKAHP: whithout KAHP the phase reset does not occur (however is not affected by Kslow and KA blockage)
Noise: the Golgi cell with random inhibitory and excitatory input added
Noise_reset: 5 voltage traces superimposed to show the phase reset effect during noise
Resonance: the response to a current injection is enached during repeted stimulation at 3Hz
***
@ Matteo (2010) - CML translation: created a configuration, for each channel, to compare the original mod file and the CML translation (each one inculdes 2 cell types, 2 groups, 2 inputs and the plots for v and gates).
This is the default configuration of the Cell Groups, stimulations, plots, etc for this project
